;Digital Inclusion means supporting universal access to the whole Internet
Taguri tumḍint temmal-d aseḥbiber ɣef unekcum amaḍalan at Internet meṛṛa


;We should all have affordable, high-quality, unrestricted access to the whole Web, so the whole world can benefit.
Yessefk meṛṛa ad nesɛu anekcum ar Web rxiṣen, n tɣara meqqṛen s war tilisa, akken yal yiwen ad ifaṛes tagnitt.


;To participate online, you have to be able to get online. Programs have emerged that offer free or subsidized Internet access, but it is often slow or restricted, creating a ‘poor Internet for poor people.’ At its most extreme, governments worldwide are turning off all or parts of the Internet to serve their own agendas, which can threaten human rights and even the health of the global economy.
Akken ad ttekkiḍ srid, yessek ad tizmireḍ ad tesɛuḍ anekcum. Ahilen lulen-d akken ak-d-mudden anekcum baṭel neɣ deg-s aɛiwen ar Internet, maca anekcum-agi ẓẓay neq ɣur-s talast, d ayen i d-yesnulfan "Internet Agellil i yigellilen". Di kra n isatalen, inabaḍen n umadal meṛṛa gezzmen anekcum meṛṛa neɣ ar kra n yeḥricen n Internet akken ad sɛeddin tiktiwin-nsen neɣ ad seḥbibren ɣef ubaɣur-nsen, d ayen i d-yettwawin ayen n dir ama i yizerfan n umdan neɣ tazmert n tdamsa n umaḍal.


